main event: An observer believed he saw a glowing object in the form of a four-leaf clover at an altitude of 30,000 feet, making 90-degree turns.
interesting points: The object was making 90-degree turns, indicating the possibility of searchlight activity as the cause.
The report was delayed in receiving the initial report, so the activity was not observed on the night of the sighting.
The observer's account is the only source of information for this sighting.
The length of the observation is unknown.
sighted object: a glowing object in the form of a four-leaf clover
